{
  "stem": "26672.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now we had no-- no way of doing it at [INAUDIBLE] unless he had, um, somebody he knew in the occupation forces that, um, would have given that to help to send a telegram to my uncle to Palestine who lived in [?",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Haifa then. ?]",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to say all was well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He left in 1933-34.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yaacov Finkelman.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was the brother of my mother, one-- one of the brothers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He-- well, he-- he-- lived in-- in-- Palestine, in Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, we never spoke much about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tried to talk to him many times about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He always avoided talking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He felt very guilty of-- because apparently he, uh-- he had-- obviously things were tough in Palestine in those days.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father, I believe, asked him what he should do, whether he should to come to Palestine or not.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he advised him not to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You see, things were hard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He had to work as a laborer, in the building material on the-- the land.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, uh, he knew that my father, [PAUSES] or my mother, rather, was the oldest of-- of the family.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was still sisters of my mother that weren't married.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she sort of looked after them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he felt a bit guilty for advising my father, not directly, but hinted to him that it wasn't the place for him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very good, almost-- almost like a father to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in fact when I, when I was demobbed from the Israeli army in 1949 he wanted me very much to come and live with him.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had two daughters and, uh, obviously his wife And his wife, particularly-- she was like a mother to me.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
